item.title: Who helps me get rs acc lv 70
item.dc:creator: @Emchie Emchie
item.description:
@Emchie wrote:

[quote=“johno2, post:5, topic:269289”][quote author=Emchie link=topic=355376.msg2720925#msg2720925 date=1237981239]
Well, Its more efficient to just tell him, so here it is:

  1. Download and Install No-Ip DUC.
  2. Add your Hosts on No-Ip.
  3. Download JDK
  4. PortForward. Or Download uTorrent.
  5. If you chose uTorrent, go to preferences, then Port, change to 43594, and click Apply, then Ok.
  6. Run No-Ip
  7. Run Server Source
  8. Run uTorrent (If Chosen)
  9. [tt]Log in and Play!YAY[/tt]
    [/quote]

Im sure you can’t use Utorrent to open ports, it only find ports what are open in your comp, it doesn’t forward them?[/quote]

It does forward them, because thats what I use to run my server, and people connect fine, probably better than what it is when I PortForward.

item.description:
@icp_again wrote:

If you wish to configure the server without anyone else getting on, don’t open your no-ip DUC hit run server then load the client, and for the IP put “localhost” then no one else can get online, unless of course you have your No-IP turned on.
